=encoding utf8

=head1 mksamplecsv

B<mksamplecsv> - Make sample user and group list

=head1 SYNOPSIS

    $ B<mksamplecsv> B<--user>
    $ B<mksamplecsv> B<-h> | B<--help> | B<-?>

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Make sample user list at ease.

    $ ./mksamplecsv -num 3
    # Full_name,Account,Password,UID,2nd Group,2nd GID,Home_Server,Network_Home_Directory,Login_Shell
    Sample User1,sample1,passwd,11025,samples,11025,garuda,home,/bin/bash
    Sample User2,sample2,passwd,11026,samples,11025,garuda,home,/bin/bash
    Sample User3,sample3,passwd,11027,samples,11025,garuda,home,/bin/bash

=head1 OPTIONS

=over 4

=item B<--user> sample : Sample account name.

=item B<--uid> 11025 : Number of Starting UID. ( 501 < UID < 2,147,483,649)

=item B<--gid> 11025 : Number of Starting GID. ( 501 < GID < 2,147,483,649)

=item B<--group> samples : Sample group name.

=item B<--num> 5 : Number of accounts you want. ( n > 0 ).

=item B<--passwd> password_text : Password text for all of sample users.

=item B<--homeroot> dir_name : Network home directory share point name.

=item B<--homesrv> server.example.com : Home server name.

=item B<--shell> /bin/bash : User's login shell

=item B<--help> : Show this message.

=item B<--debug> : Make debug mode on.

=item B<--real> : Make users using predefined user name. maximum number of samples is 20.

=back

=cut

